  "solution": "Wien's displacement law states that the peak wavelength λ_max (in meters) of blackbody radiation is inversely proportional to the temperature T (in kelvins): λ_max = b / T, where b ≈ 2.897771955×10⁻³ m·K. The problem states that a photon must have a wavelength shorter than 89.27 nm to ionize hydrogen, so we set λ_max = 89.27 nm = 89.27 × 10⁻⁹ m. Solving for T: T = b / λ_max = (2.897771955×10⁻³ m·K) / (89.27 × 10⁻⁹ m) ≈ 3.246 × 10⁴ K.",
